        <strong>Osteocalcin activation — bone building</strong>
        <p>K2 activates osteocalcin, a protein produced by osteoblasts that binds calcium and incorporates it into bone hydroxyapatite matrix. Without K2, osteocalcin remains inactive (undercarboxylated) and calcium bypasses bones.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>MGP activation — arterial protection</strong>
        <p>K2 activates matrix Gla protein (MGP), the most potent natural inhibitor of vascular calcification. Activated MGP prevents calcium from crystallizing in arterial walls, heart valves, and kidneys.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>D3 + K2 synergy</strong>
        <p>Vitamin D3 increases calcium absorption. K2 ensures that calcium reaches bone matrix rather than soft tissues. Together, they form the complete calcium-management system for skeletal and cardiovascular health.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>MK-7: the preferred form</strong>
        <p>MK-7 has a 72-hour half-life allowing once-daily dosing at 100-200mcg. MK-4 has only a 1-2 hour half-life requiring doses of 15-45mg multiple times daily. Most clinical research supports MK-7.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

