      <span class="warn-box-ico">&#9888;</span>
      <p><strong>Critical warning:</strong> Individuals taking warfarin (Coumadin) must NOT take vitamin K2 supplements without explicit physician approval and INR monitoring. Vitamin K directly opposes warfarin's anticoagulant mechanism. This interaction can be life-threatening. If you take newer anticoagulants (DOACs), consult your physician — these typically do not interact with vitamin K.</p>
